    {
      "name": "dotnet-expenses",
      "cwd": "../demo/ExpenseTracker/AspNetCore",
      "prebuild": { "cmd": "dotnet", "args": ["build", "--nologo", "-v", "minimal"] },
      "start": "dotnet",
      "args": ["run", "--no-build", "--no-launch-profile", "--urls", "http://localhost:5007"],
      "baseUrl": "http://localhost:5007",
      "ready": "/api/expenses",
      "fixtures": ["expenses"]
    },
    {
      "name": "bun-expenses",
      "cwd": "../demo/ExpenseTracker-bun",
      "start": "bun",
      "args": ["run", "server.ts"],
      "env": { "PORT": "5008" },
      "baseUrl": "http://localhost:5008",
      "ready": "/api/expenses",
      "fixtures": ["expenses"]
    },
    {
      "name": "dotnet-helpdesk",
      "cwd": "../demo/HelpDesk/AspNetCore",
      "prebuild": { "cmd": "dotnet", "args": ["build", "--nologo", "-v", "minimal"] },
      "cleanupFiles": ["helpdesk-parity-dotnet.db"],
      "start": "dotnet",
      "args": ["run", "--no-build", "--no-launch-profile", "--urls", "http://localhost:5009"],
      "env": { "HELPDESK_DB": "helpdesk-parity-dotnet.db", "HELPDESK_SEED": "0" },
      "baseUrl": "http://localhost:5009",
      "ready": "/api/requester",
      "fixtures": ["helpdesk"]
    },
    {
      "name": "bun-helpdesk",
      "cwd": "../demo/HelpDesk-bun",
      "cleanupFiles": ["helpdesk-parity-bun.db"],
      "start": "bun",
      "args": ["run", "server.ts"],
      "env": { "PORT": "5010", "HELPDESK_DB": "helpdesk-parity-bun.db", "HELPDESK_SEED": "0" },
      "baseUrl": "http://localhost:5010",
      "ready": "/api/requester",
      "fixtures": ["helpdesk"]
    },
    {
      "$comment": "SEEDED helpdesk twin. Deliberately does NOT set HELPDESK_SEED=0, so the demo's ~80-ticket seed runs and the agent queue's OVER-CAP branch (matching > Cap(25) -> 'refine the filter') actually EXECUTES. The unseeded pair above cannot reach it: with the seed off there are 2 tickets, so `matching <= Cap` is always true and that branch is dead code under parity — which is how a real style-vs-tone drift on that node shipped for releases while parity printed 'all backends agree'. Its own DB file so it never shares state with the unseeded twin. See fixtures/helpdesk-seeded.json.",
      "name": "dotnet-helpdesk-seeded",
      "cwd": "../demo/HelpDesk/AspNetCore",
      "prebuild": { "cmd": "dotnet", "args": ["build", "--nologo", "-v", "minimal"] },
      "cleanupFiles": ["helpdesk-parity-dotnet-seeded.db"],
      "start": "dotnet",
      "args": ["run", "--no-build", "--no-launch-profile", "--urls", "http://localhost:5016"],
      "env": { "HELPDESK_DB": "helpdesk-parity-dotnet-seeded.db" },
      "baseUrl": "http://localhost:5016",
      "ready": "/api/requester",
      "fixtures": ["helpdesk-seeded"]
    },
    {
      "$comment": "SEEDED helpdesk twin (bun side) — see dotnet-helpdesk-seeded above. HELPDESK_SEED intentionally unset so the seed runs.",
      "name": "bun-helpdesk-seeded",
      "cwd": "../demo/HelpDesk-bun",
      "cleanupFiles": ["helpdesk-parity-bun-seeded.db"],
      "start": "bun",
      "args": ["run", "server.ts"],
      "env": { "PORT": "5017", "HELPDESK_DB": "helpdesk-parity-bun-seeded.db" },
      "baseUrl": "http://localhost:5017",
      "ready": "/api/requester",
      "fixtures": ["helpdesk-seeded"]
    },
    {
